This message will be more like a note to self.I've added so that a ruby instance of each event type is created when an event is allocated and initialized. Left to do is to keep reference to these objects inside the event instance and to force the event type instances to keep a reference back to their original event. This is to make sure that the garbage collector keep them together in memory at all times. Also something I must do is to check the event's type in the initialize method so that we will always only create ONE of these child instances.nnThis way we won't need to allocate any unnecessary memory except if the developer specifically request a new event type instance. For example: SFML::Event::Key.newnngit-svn-id: https://sfml.svn.sourceforge.net/svnroot/sfml/branches/sfml2@1606 4e206d99-4929-0410-ac5d-dfc041789085n

commit_message: Window::SetCursorPosition now triggers MouseMoved events

Made sf::Mutex recursive on Unix, the behaviour is now consistent across platforms
Minor fix in sf::Text
UdpSocket::Send(Packet) is now limited to UdpSocket::MaxDatagramSize, so that data is never split into multiple datagrams, which removes a lot of potential major problems

Fixed warning in GlxContext constructor
Minor fix in UdpSocket::Send(Packet)

Fixed universal build on OS X.

minor compiler warnings fixed

Fix annoying sound alert when escape is pressed on OS X
Fix autorelease problem (issue #62)

Minor fixes to the doc
Minor fix in comments
OpenGL.hpp now includes windows.h only with VC++
Fixed sf::Mouse::IsButtonPressed and sf::Keyboard::IsKeyPressed incorrectly returning true on Windows
Minor fix in API documentation

Improved SFML integration with Cocoa

Fixed Xcode templates script
Removed dummy.cpp

fixed creation of frameworks and a minor error in xcode 4 template script
fixed creation of SFML.framework

Fixed error when calling Shader::LoadFromFile multiple times on the same instance
Fixed linker errors with InputStream in SFML dynamic libraries
fix OS X alert related to key event (close #98)
Added explicit include directories for OpenGL and X11 in CMake files

Fixed signed/unsigned comparison
Fixed error in subrect adjustment in Texture::LoadFromImage
FindSFML.cmake now defines the SFML_STATIC macro when requesting static libraries
SFML shared libraries now use ELF visibility on Unixes with gcc >= 4
Improve Xcode 4 Templates (close #113)

Remove unused file

Explicit use signed char for included font data to enable cross-compile for an arm-based systemFrom ISO/IEC 9899:1999, 6.2.5.15 (p. 49):nThe implementation shall define char to have the same range,nrepresentation, and behavior as either signed char or unsigned char.nnSigned-off-by: Thomas Knepper <thknepper@gmx.de>n
Merge pull request #128 from thknepper/fix-cross-compileExplicit use signed char for included font data to enable cross-compile on ARM-based systems

Implemented the new graphics API: - Removed the internal classes sf::Renderer and sf::Matrix3 - Split sf::Drawable into sf::Drawable and sf::Transformable - Added sf::Transform - Added sf::Vertex - Added sf::VertexArray - Types of shapes are now handled with their own derived class - Modified the Pong example
Merge branch 'master' into drawablesConflicts:ntinclude/SFML/Graphics/Sprite.hppntinclude/SFML/Graphics/Text.hppntsrc/SFML/Graphics/Sprite.cppn
sf::ConvexShape was not updated when SetPointsCount or SetPoint was called
Added constructors with parameters for shapes, and default-constructed shapes are now always empty
Fixed compile error caused by previous commit
sf::Shape now outputs less warnings about the number of points
Fixed compile errors in sf::Vertex with LLVM GCC 4.2 on OS X Lion
Made one-arg constructors explicit in shapes classes
Fixed bug in sf::Shape
Removed references to the old sf::Renderer class
Removed wrong comment about scale factors in sf::Transformable
Fixed typo
Fixed bug in Music::SetPlayingOffset (didn't work above a given timestamp)

Removed the sf::StarShape class

Added SetPointsCount in sf::CircleShape
Changed the Unix implementation of sf::Sleep to a more robust one
Fixed minor warnings on Linux
Fixed (?) a fragment shader in the Shader example

Fixed typo in comments
Added a virtual destructor to sf::Transformable
Rewrote the implementation of sf::Clock, it now ensures microseconds resolution and monotonicity
The new Linux clock implementation required to link an extra library
Fixed typo
Removed unused Context::GetCurrentContextId()
Minor modifications
Changed the type of Vertex::TexCoords from integers to floats, to make it compatible with buggy ATI drivers
sf::Joystick now handles controllers designated as Gamepad (Fix #138)
Added a render states cache to improve performances

Fixed default color of sf::Text (was black instead of white)
Fixed minor error in sf::Font::LoadFromStream
Added detection of Visual C++ 2011 in CMake files
Added error checking in initialization of GLEW
Fixed glBindProgramObject used on systems that don't support shaders

*Really* solved the last commit problem :)
minor fix in cmake script
The architecture (32/64 bits) is now detected only on Windows

commit_message: minor update of Cocoa-SFML example

Add pkg-config files, optionally installed by CMake on Linux builds.The modules provided are:nn  - sfml-systemn  - sfml-graphicsn  - sfml-windown  - sfml-audion  - sfml-networkn  - sfml-all (depends on all the above modules)nnThey are installed to ${CMAKE_INSTALL_PREFIX}/lib${LIB_SUFFIX}/pkgconfig/nwhich is the standard location for pkg-config files on Linux.nnAn example use if using autotools:nn# configure.acnAC_INIT([sfml-example],[1.0],[example@example.com])nAM_INIT_AUTOMAKE([foreign])nAC_PROG_CXXnPKG_CHECK_MODULES([sfml],n[sfml-all >= 2.0.0],n[], [AC_MSG_ERROR([SFML is required])])nAC_CONFIG_FILES([Makefile])nAC_OUTPUTnn# Makefile.amnbin_PROGRAMS = sfml_examplensfml_example_SOURCES = src/sfml_example.cppnsfml_example_CFLAGS = $(sfml_CFLAGS)nsfml_example_LIBS = $(sfml_LIBS)nnAn example if using hand-written Makefiles:nn# Makefilensfml-example: src/sfml-example.cppng++ `pkg-config --cflags --libs sfml-all` -o $@ $^n

commit_message: Remove a part of CMake script that doesn't work any more.No attempt to fix this part of the script is made because it change toonoften (at each OS release) and no gain would result from a potentialnfix.nnSDKs are not stored in /Developer anymore with recent versions of Xcode.nnNow the users should manually set the following variables :n - CMAKE_OSX_SYSROOT,n - CMAKE_OSX_DEPLOYMENT_TARGET,n - CMAKE_OSX_ARCHITECTURESn
Add freetype.framework and edit CMake accordingly. (Close #241)Freetype version 2.4.11, build for OS X 10.5 and above as universalnbinary (i386 + x86_64)n

Improve Xcode templates : now you can target 10.5 without headache !

Improved the API documentation stylesheet
Fixed joysticks not detected when checked at application startup.
Minor addition in the API documentation

Added Unicode window title support.- Changed SFML API to receive an sf::String as the window title insteadn  of a std::string (in Window::Window and Window::setTitle).n- Changed RenderWindow and WindowImpl APIs accordingly.n- Changed WindowImplWin32 to use a Unicode window title only if then  target OS supports it.n- Changed WindowImplCocoa to always use Unicode window titles and addedn  a utility function to Window/OSX/cpp_objc_conversion.mm.n- Changed WindowImplX11 to set the Unicode window title as part of then  _NET_WM_NAME specification, which sadly is not part of the official Xn  standard, but the closest anything can get. Still set regular ASCIIn  title as fallback.n

Simplified UTF-8 encoding procedure for X11 window title.- Instead of first converting to a wide string and converting that ton  UTF-8, now convert to UTF-8 directly using sf::Utf32::toUtf8.n- Modify OS X sf::String to NSString helper to work for big-endiann  architectures (like OS X 10.5 on PowerPC) as well.n

Fix a bug in the font system.When the finding a rectangle for a glyph at a particular character size,nif the glyph happens to be wider than the current texture size, but lessnhigh than the unused height in the texture, the texture will not bencorrectly doubled in size (since only the height is checked).nnIn practice, this only occurs when finding the rectangle for the *verynfirst* glyph (so the texture is at its default 128x128 size): otherwise,nthe glyph would need to be unusually wide compared to its height tontrigger the bug.nnThis will trigger a debug assertion in Texture::update(). With assertionsndisabled, there are knock-on effects and most text at that character sizenwill fail to render.n

Android: Updated the toolchain file and CMake scripts* Replaced the toolchain file with a new version based on [zuhowei's fork](https://github.com/zhuowei/android-cmake), which enables x64 builds as well as support for the latest NDK. This breaks compatibility with old build directories.n* Removed the STL dependency from **sfml-activity** rather than relying on *some* implementation implicitly linked by default.n* Deleted *project.properties*, which wasn't supposed to be part of the repository code. You have to use the Android SDK to recreate it (`android update project --path to/your/example --target 1 --name SFML-Example`).n* Made it possible to select a STL implementation to be used (default: `c++_shared`). Keep in mind that not all available configurations are necessarily compatible with SFML.n* Fixed linker flags to be compatible with Nvidia's Nsight Tegra for Visual Studio.n* It is now possible to compile the Android version using Nvidia's Nsight Tegra for Visual Studio (requires up-to-date CMake and `CMAKE_SFML_SYSTEM` to be set to `Android`; keep in mind that this is still experimental and requires further CMake updates).n* Updated and renamed some Android specific CMake variables.n* Made `armeabi-v7a` the default ABI for Android builds.n

Adjusted WindowImplX11.* Replaced Xlib event names by XCB equivalents.n* Removed XCB_CW_OVERRIDE_REDIRECT in order to let the WM handle mappingn  the window to the full screen.n* Fixed mouse grabbing in fullscreen mode. FindSFML.cmake: Ignored environment variables to find library pathsEnvironment variables (e.g. PATH on Windows) are looked up early by CMake, and libraries found there are prioritized over those in SFML's own folder. To avoid paths to wrong libraries, this commit modifies the CMake find_library() call, such that environment variables are no longer considered as suitable paths.n

Made implementation of glCheck and alCheck macros more robustAt the moment, glCheck(...) and alCheck(...) look like a function calls, which is misleading and can cause subtle bugs, for example when used in if statements. This change mitigates the situation by allowing those expressions to be used as single statements within if/else branches.nnInitializations of OpenGL handles that previously involved glCheck() calls now need to be split into separate declaration and assignment.n

Added OS X implementation of sf::Window::setCursorGrabbedThis implementation uses the following workaround:n - resize flag is removed from the window when the cursor is grabbedn - when grabbed, the cursor is projected inside the view if neededn - to avoid letting the user clic outside the view, the cursor isn   disconnected and manually moved using relative motionn - the initial potential projection of the cursor results in a bign   delta for the next move and needed to be somehow ignored (seen   note about m_deltaXBuffer and m_deltaYBuffer in SFOpenGLView.h)n

Correctly add XCB components if no components are requestedThis commit fixes the FindXCB.cmake module for the case no componentsnare requested. The previous version assigned `XCB_FIND_COMPONENTS`nlist to an empty variable name.nnI was lucky enough to catch the bug in a corner case where bothn`XCB_COMPONENTS` and `XCB_FIND_COMPONENTS` were empty and `set()`ncommand failed, but note this awesome CMake language supports more annoyingncorner cases like `XCB_COMPONENTS` empty and `XCB_FIND_COMPONENTS`nwith two elements, which results in the following `set()` invocation:nn``` cmakenset(${XCB_FIND_COMPONENTS[0]} ${XCB_FIND_COMPONENTS[1]})n```nnSo always beware of CMake secret charms...n

fixed sf::Image::createDiscussion thread: http://en.sfml-dev.org/forums/index.php?topic=20875.0nBasically, the issue with sf::Image::create was, that it would eithernoccupy space, it doesn't need, because std::vector::resize doesn'tnactually shrink the vector, or reallocate in an inefficient way bynneedlessly copying the whole old image over. Neither did it grant strongnexception safety guarantee because it changed the non-throwing membersn(m_size) prior to doing the critical stuff (reallocating) which maynthrow. Changing the order and using a temporaryn(create-temporary-and-swap idiom; see http://www.gotw.ca/gotw/059.htm)nfixes both of these problems.n

packaging support improvementsThis grew out of my work creating an sfml port for macports, but shouldnbe helpful for package maintainers of various distributions:nn* add an SFML_USE_SYSTEM_DEPS option to ignore everything in extlibs/n  except for headers/stb_image, and use the system versionsnn* install pkg-config files if a pkg-config program is foundn  and either lib/pkgconfig or libdata/pkgconfig exists under then  INSTALL_PREFIX, or the SFML_INSTALL_PKGCONFIG_FILES flag is setn  explicitlynn* install pkg-config files for static libs too, add the necessaryn  Requires.private and Libs.private entries to the .pc files to supportn  static linkingnn* on OS X, honor all INSTALL_NAME and RPATH related cmake variables andn  only set the INSTALL_NAME_DIR to @rpath if none of them is set, thisn  preserves the default behavior of using @rpath but also allowsn  overriding by the usual cmake mechanismsn

Android: Removed custom toolchain fileThis commit drops the previous custom CMake toolchain file for Androidnin favor of CMake's new built-in toolchain for this (CMake >3.7.2).nnThis makes building SFML for Android a lot simpler and more straightnforward, working almost as smooth as other platforms.nnTo configure your build directory, all you have to do is defining just anfew variables the first time you invoke CMake.nn**Required Variables**nn* `CMAKE_SYSTEM_NAME` must be `Android`, so CMake knows we actually wantn  to cross-compile.n* `CMAKE_ANDROID_NDK` must point to the NDK's installation directory,n  e.g. `/usr/android/ndk` or `c:/android/ndk`.nn**Recommended Variables**n* `CMAKE_ANDROID_STL_TYPE` defines the STL implementation to be used.n  You should use `c++_shared`, although others might work.nn**Optional Variables**n* `CMAKE_SYSTEM_VERSION` can be set to pick a specific SDK version othern  than the latest.n* `CMAKE_ANDROID_ARCH_ABI` defines the target architecture and ABI, forn  example `armeabi` or `armeabi-v7a`.nnBased on your system, you might want to enforce a specific generator tonprevent issues, e.g. using `MinGW Makefiles`.n

Unix: Filter X visual by X screenOn an X set-up with multiple monitors running separate X screens (asnopposed to merging them into one large X screen using Xinerama), thenselected X visual needs to be one for the screen where the colormap,nwindow, and other X resources are created. In fact, all these need tonmatch, and the GL context as well.nnMost of the SFML windowing and graphics code uses (X)DefaultScreen()nfor that, which is fine. Combined with XOpenDisplay(NULL), this willncreate the window on the screen (and monitor) selected by the DISPLAYnenviroment variable. :0.0 will be the first monitor, :0.1 the second,netc.nnHowever, XGetVisualInfo() will return visuals for *all* screens, notnjust the default one. They seem to be ordered by screen number, but Indon't think the standard makes any guarantees there.nnIf the visual doesn't match up with the screen, this will abort withnan X error. BadMatch, in many cases.nnThis means that in addition to other filtering,nGlxContext::selectBestVisual() needs to filter the visuals by screennnumber, otherwise SFML won't work at all on any screens but the first.nnThis fixes issue #724.n

Changed Doxygen single-line comment formatSingle line comments starting with `///` are interpreted bynMicrosoft Visual Studio as documentation containing XML code.nnTherefore single line comments starting with `///<` unfortunatelyncause a parsing error, as IntelliSense will assume the `<` is thenstart of an XML tag. This is not the case, but unfortunately,nIntelliSense will still complain about the following spacencharacter rather than displaying the raw string. This commit altersnall such comments to start with `//!<` instead, which prevents thenissue.nnThis fixes issue #1622.n

Force OpenGL states to be reset when RenderTarget detects that a new context has to be tracked. In the case a context is re-created, FBO RenderTextures would not trigger resetting of the OpenGL states if they were drawn to first since re-initialization of the RenderTarget only happens when a context owner such as a RenderWindow is re-created. Fixes #1625.
